"Here's a new Python question for you:\n\n```\n{\n    \"title\": \"Maximum Sum of Subarray (Medium)\",\n    \"description\": \"Given an array of integers, find the maximum sum of a subarray within the given array. A subarray is any contiguous segment of the array.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef max_sum_subarray(arr: list[int)) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `arr` (list[int]): A list of integers representing the input array.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the maximum sum of a subarray within the given array.\\n\",\n    \"code\": \"\"\"\nimport itertools\n\ndef max_sum_subarray(arr: list[int)) -> int:\n    n = len(arr)\n    max_sum = float('-inf')\n    \n    for window_size in range(1, n + 1):\n        for start in range(n - window_size + 1):\n            window = arr[start:start + window_size]\n            current_sum = sum(window)\n            \n            if current_sum > max_sum:\n                max_sum = current_sum\n    \n    return max_sum\n\"\"\", \n    \"tests\": [\n        \"assert max_sum_subarray([-2, 1, -3, 4, -1, 2, 1, -5, 4]) == 6\",\n        \"assert max_sum_subarray([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) == 15\",\n        \"assert max_sum_subarray([-1, -2, -3, -4, -5]) == -1\",\n        \"assert max_sum_subarray([]) == 0\"\n    ]\n}\n```"